{
  "stem": "7094.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then the arrangement was at the end of the year I'll go to Lvov and take the exam in gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, this teacher is still alive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I met him in New York when I visited.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was the one who opened the doors for me to Greek and to literature and to history, and-- he was a student himself, but he needed extra money to maintain himself, and he was teaching.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I was relieved that at least now I'd be able to educate myself.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Education was very important, because it was a way out of this little town and opportunity for future.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If I tell my grandchildren that most of the students who managed-- which I envied them, that they managed to get to gymnasium, the station was about 1 and 1/2 kilometers away from the town.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they used to get up for the 8 o'clock train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So they had to walk, [? or ?] because they couldn't afford traveling-- there were no cars in our town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There were [NON-ENGLISH], or in the winter sleigh.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then they would come back at night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then they would go every day, sleigh-- rain, snow, and [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they considered themselves lucky to have the opportunity to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It would be hardship nowadays to consider.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But they've considered themselves-- and I envied them that they had the opportunity to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The emphasis was a great drive, a great emphasis on education.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because it was, one, not only-- I mean, Jewish families always put emphasis on learning and teaching, and-- But also, it was a way out of this environment and a door to the world outside.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the Russian came and they formed this sort of secondary education, I was relieved.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
